    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus of woody flowering plants, either trees or shrubs. Most are root parasites that photosynthesize their own food but tap the roots of other species for water and inorganic nutrients. Several species, most notably S. album, produce highly aromatic wood, used for scents and perfumes and for herbal medicine.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042061/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus van houtige bloeiende planten, voorkomend als bomen of heesters. Meestal betreft het wortelparasieten die zich voeden door fotosynthese, terwijl ze water en anorganische voedingstoffen aan de wortels van andere soorten onttrekken. Diverse soorten, met name S. album, produceren sterk geurend hout, dat gebruikt wordt als geurstof en voor parfums, en als kruidengeneesmiddel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>會開花的喬木或灌木屬名。大多為根寄生植物，通過光合作用產生自己的食物，但會從其他種植物的根部汲取水分和無機的養分。包含許多種類，以檀香樹最為人所知；檀香樹會生產芳香的木材，應用於香氛、香水和草藥。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
